     1| <?php
     2| namespace JSONStream;
     3| use InvalidArgumentException;
     4| use JsonException;
     5| use RuntimeException;
     6| use Generator;
     7| /**
     8|  * Reads a large JSON file structured as an array of objects ([{...}, {...}])
     9|  * in a streaming, memory-efficient manner.
    10|  *
    11|  * Parses the stream incrementally and yields individual objects.
    12|  * Handles UTF-8 characters and JSON string escaping correctly.
    13|  */
    14| class CollectionReader {
    15|     protected const int CHUNK_SIZE = 8192;
    16|     protected $resource;
    17|     protected bool $asArray = false;
    18|     protected string $buffer = '';
    19|     protected int $nestingLevel = 0;
    20|     protected bool $inString = false; // State: Track if currently inside a JSON string "..."
    21|     protected bool $escaped = false;  // State: Track if the previous character was an escape '\'
    22|     /**
    23|      * @param string $path Path to the JSON file.
    24|      * @param bool $asArray Decode objects as associative arrays (true) or stdClass objects (false).
    25|      * @throws InvalidArgumentException If the file path is invalid or the file cannot be opened.
    26|      */
    27|     public function __construct(string $path, bool $asArray = true) {
    28|         if (!is_readable($path) || !is_file($path)) {
    29|             throw new InvalidArgumentException('File does not exist or is not readable at given path: ' . $path);
    30|         }
    31|         $this->asArray = $asArray;
    32|         $resource = @fopen($path, 'rb');
    33|         if ($resource === false) {
    34|             throw new InvalidArgumentException('Failed to open file for reading: ' . $path);
    35|         }
    36|         $this->resource = $resource;
    37|     }
    38|     /**
    39|      * Closes the file resource if it is open.
    40|      */
    41|     public function close(): void {
    42|         if (is_resource($this->resource)) {
    43|             fclose($this->resource);
    44|             $this->resource = null; // Ensure resource is marked as closed
    45|         }
    46|     }
    47|     /**
    48|      * Returns a Generator that yields each top-level object from the JSON array.
    49|      *
    50|      * @return Generator Decoded objects (or arrays based on $asArray).
    51|      * @throws RuntimeException If reading from the file stream fails.
    52|      * @throws JsonException If the JSON is malformed or truncated.
    53|      */
    54|     public function get(): Generator {
    55|         $this->buffer = '';
    56|         $this->nestingLevel = 0;
    57|         $this->inString = false;
    58|         $this->escaped = false;
    59|         if (!is_resource($this->resource)) {
    60|              throw new RuntimeException('File stream is not available or already closed.');
    61|         }
    62|         if (ftell($this->resource) !== 0) {
    63|              rewind($this->resource);
    64|         }
    65|         while (!feof($this->resource)) {
    66|             $chunk = @fread($this->resource, self::CHUNK_SIZE);
    67|             if ($chunk === false) { // Handle read errors
    68|                  $this->close();
    69|                  throw new RuntimeException('Failed to read from file stream.');
    70|             }
    71|             if ($chunk === '') { // Avoid processing empty chunks unnecessarily
    72|                 continue;
    73|             }
    74|             yield from $this->parseChunk($chunk);
    75|         }
    76|         if ($this->nestingLevel !== 0) {
    77|             $this->close();
    78|             throw new JsonException("Invalid JSON structure: unexpected end of file - nesting level is {$this->nestingLevel}, expected 0.");
    79|         }
    80|         if ($this->inString) {
    81|              $this->close();
    82|             throw new JsonException("Invalid JSON structure: unexpected end of file - parser ended inside a string literal.");
    83|         }
    84|         $trimmedBuffer = trim($this->buffer);
    85|         if ($trimmedBuffer !== '' && $trimmedBuffer !== ']') { // Allow trailing whitespace or the final ']'
    86|              $this->close();
    87|              throw new JsonException("Invalid JSON structure: unexpected trailing data in buffer: '" . mb_substr($trimmedBuffer, 0, 50) . "...'");
    88|         }
    89|     }
    90|     /**
    91|      * Parses the buffered data including the new chunk, yielding complete objects.
    92|      * Manages parsing state ($nestingLevel, $inString, $escaped) across chunks.
    93|      *
    94|      * @param string $chunk The newly read chunk of data.
    95|      * @return Generator Decoded objects/arrays found in the buffer.
    96|      * @throws JsonException If JSON is invalid during parsing or decoding.
    97|      */
    98|     private function parseChunk(string $chunk): Generator {
    99|         $this->buffer .= $chunk;
   100|         $startCharIndex = -1; // Character index where the current top-level object started
   101|         $keepFromCharIndex = 0; // Character index from where to keep the buffer for the next round
   102|         $split = mb_str_split($this->buffer);
   103|         foreach ($split as $position => $char) {
   104|             $processChar = true; // Flag to indicate if char influences state/structure
   105|             if ($this->escaped) {
   106|                 $this->escaped = false;
   107|                 $processChar = false; // Don't process this char further for state changes
   108|             } elseif ($char === '\\') {
   109|                 $this->escaped = true;
   110|                 $processChar = false; // Don't process this char further for state changes
   111|             } elseif ($char === '"') {
   112|                 $this->inString = !$this->inString;
   113|                 $processChar = false; // Don't process this char for structure changes
   114|             }
   115|             if ($processChar && !$this->inString) {
   116|                 if ($char === '{') {
   117|                     if ($this->nestingLevel === 0) {
   118|                         $startCharIndex = $position; // Mark start character index
   119|                     }
   120|                     $this->nestingLevel++;
   121|                 } elseif ($char === '}') {
   122|                     if ($this->nestingLevel <= 0) {
   123|                         $this->close();
   124|                         throw new JsonException("Invalid JSON structure: unexpected '}' found near buffer character offset " . $position);
   125|                     }
   126|                     $this->nestingLevel--;
   127|                     if ($this->nestingLevel === 0 && $startCharIndex !== -1) {
   128|                         $endCharIndex = $position;
   129|                         $length = $endCharIndex - $startCharIndex + 1;
   130|                         $jsonString = mb_substr($this->buffer, $startCharIndex, $length);
   131|                         $decoded = @json_decode($jsonString, $this->asArray);
   132|                         $error = json_last_error();
   133|                         if ($error !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
   134|                             $this->close();
   135|                             $snippet = mb_substr($jsonString, 0, 100) . (mb_strlen($jsonString) > 100 ? '...' : '');
   136|                             throw new JsonException(json_last_error_msg() . " - near JSON snippet: \"" . $snippet . "\"", $error);
   137|                         }
   138|                         yield $decoded;
   139|                         $startCharIndex = -1;
   140|                         $keepFromCharIndex = $endCharIndex + 1;
   141|                     }
   142|                 }
   143|             }
   144|         } // end foreach character
   145|         if ($keepFromCharIndex > 0) {
   146|              if ($keepFromCharIndex >= count($split)) {
   147|                  $this->buffer = '';
   148|              } else {
   149|                  $this->buffer = mb_substr($this->buffer, $keepFromCharIndex);
   150|              }
   151|         }
   152|     }
   153|     /**
   154|      * Ensures the file resource is closed when the object is destroyed.
   155|      */
   156|     public function __destruct() {
   157|         $this->close();
   158|     }
   159| }

     1| <?php
     2| namespace JSONStream;
     3| use InvalidArgumentException;
     4| use JsonException;
     5| use RuntimeException;
     6| /**
     7|  * Writes a potentially large array of PHP items to a JSON file ([{...}, {...}])
     8|  * in a streaming, robust, and atomic (via temp file) manner.
     9|  */
    10| class CollectionWriter {
    11|     protected const WRITE_MODE = 'wb'; // Use binary mode for consistency
    12|     protected $resource;
    13|     protected string $finalPath;
    14|     protected ?string $tempPath;
    15|     protected int $key = 0;
    16|     protected bool $closed = false;
    17|     /**
    18|      * @param string $path The final path for the JSON file.
    19|      * @throws InvalidArgumentException If the path is invalid, directory not writable, or temp file cannot be created/opened.
    20|      * @throws RuntimeException If writing the initial '[' fails.
    21|      */
    22|     public function __construct(string $path) {
    23|         $this->finalPath = $path;
    24|         $dir = dirname($path);
    25|         if (!is_dir($dir)) {
    26|             throw new InvalidArgumentException("Target directory does not exist: " . $dir);
    27|         }
    28|         if (!is_writable($dir)) {
    29|             throw new InvalidArgumentException("Target directory is not writable: " . $dir);
    30|         }
    31|         $tempPath = @tempnam($dir, basename($path) . '.tmp_');
    32|         if ($tempPath === false) {
    33|             throw new InvalidArgumentException("Failed to create temporary file in directory: " . $dir);
    34|         }
    35|         $this->tempPath = $tempPath;
    36|         $resource = @fopen($this->tempPath, self::WRITE_MODE);
    37|         if ($resource === false) {
    38|             $this->emergencyCleanup(); // Attempt cleanup before throwing
    39|             throw new InvalidArgumentException("Failed to open temporary file for writing: " . $this->tempPath);
    40|         }
    41|         $this->resource = $resource;
    42|         try {
    43|             $this->write('[');
    44|         } catch (\Throwable $e) {
    45|             $this->emergencyCleanup(); // Ensure cleanup if initial write fails
    46|             throw $e; // Re-throw original exception
    47|         }
    48|     }
    49|     /**
    50|      * Writes a string to the temporary file, checking for errors.
    51|      * @throws RuntimeException if writing fails or stream is not open.
    52|      */
    53|     private function write(string $string): void {
    54|         if (!is_resource($this->resource)) {
    55|              throw new RuntimeException("Attempted to write but stream is not open or invalid.");
    56|         }
    57|         if ($string === '') {
    58|             return;
    59|         }
    60|         $length = strlen($string);
    61|         $bytesWritten = @fwrite($this->resource, $string);
    62|         if ($bytesWritten === false || $bytesWritten < $length) {
    63|             $this->emergencyCleanup(); // Attempt cleanup before throwing
    64|             throw new RuntimeException("Failed to write data to temporary file (disk full?): " . ($this->tempPath ?? 'N/A'));
    65|         }
    66|     }
    67|     /**
    68|      * Encodes and pushes an item onto the JSON array stream.
    69|      *
    70|      * @param mixed $item The item to encode and write (must be encodable by json_encode).
    71|      * @throws RuntimeException If writing fails or the writer is already closed.
    72|      * @throws JsonException If json_encode fails for the item (requires PHP 7.3+ for automatic throw).
    73|      */
    74|     public function push($item): void {
    75|         if ($this->closed) {
    76|             throw new RuntimeException("Cannot push item: Writer has already been closed.");
    77|         }
    78|         if (!is_resource($this->resource)) {
    79|              throw new RuntimeException("Cannot push item: File resource is not valid (writer closed prematurely?).");
    80|         }
    81|         $encodedItem = json_encode(
    82|             $item,
    83|             JSON_THROW_ON_ERROR | JSON_UNESCAPED_SLASHES | JSON_UNESCAPED_UNICODE
    84|         );
    85|         $prefix = ($this->key === 0) ? '' : ',';
    86|         $this->write($prefix . $encodedItem);
    87|         $this->key++;
    88|     }
    89|     /**
    90|      * Finalizes the JSON file: writes closing bracket, closes temp file,
    91|      * and renames temp file to final destination path.
    92|      *
    93|      * @throws RuntimeException If writing, closing, or renaming fails.
    94|      */
    95|     public function close(): void {
    96|         if ($this->closed) {
    97|             return; // Safe to call multiple times
    98|         }
    99|         if (!is_resource($this->resource)) {
   100|              $this->closed = true; // Prevent further operations
   101|              $this->emergencyCleanup(); // Attempt to clean up temp file if it exists
   102|              throw new RuntimeException("Cannot close writer: File resource is not valid (already closed or stream failed?).");
   103|         }
   104|         try {
   105|             $this->write(']'); // Write the closing bracket
   106|             if (!@fclose($this->resource)) {
   107|                  $this->resource = null;
   108|                  throw new RuntimeException("Failed to close temporary file stream: " . ($this->tempPath ?? 'N/A'));
   109|             }
   110|             $this->resource = null; // Mark resource as closed
   111|             if (!@rename($this->tempPath, $this->finalPath)) {
   112|                  throw new RuntimeException("Failed to rename temporary file '{$this->tempPath}' to final path '{$this->finalPath}'. Check permissions and paths.");
   113|             }
   114|             $this->tempPath = null;
   115|         } catch (\Throwable $e) {
   116|             $this->emergencyCleanup();
   117|             throw $e; // Preserve original exception type and message
   118|         } finally {
   119|             $this->closed = true;
   120|             if(is_resource($this->resource)) {
   121|                 @fclose($this->resource);
   122|                 $this->resource = null;
   123|             }
   124|         }
   125|     }
   126|     /**
   127|      * Performs cleanup: closes resource if open and unlinks temp file if it exists.
   128|      * Suppresses errors during cleanup itself, as it's often called after another error.
   129|      */
   130|     private function emergencyCleanup(): void {
   131|          try {
   132|              if (is_resource($this->resource)) {
   133|                  @fclose($this->resource);
   134|              }
   135|          } finally {
   136|             $this->resource = null;
   137|             if ($this->tempPath && @file_exists($this->tempPath)) {
   138|                 @unlink($this->tempPath);
   139|             }
   140|             $this->tempPath = null;
   141|             $this->closed = true;
   142|          }
   143|     }
   144|     /**
   145|      * Destructor: Ensures resources are cleaned up if close() was not explicitly called
   146|      * or if an error occurred during close(). Attempts to prevent orphaned temp files.
   147|      */
   148|     public function __destruct() {
   149|         if (is_resource($this->resource) || ($this->tempPath && @file_exists($this->tempPath))) {
   150|              $this->emergencyCleanup();
   151|         }
   152|     }
   153| }

    26|      *
    27|      * You may also supply a custom bytes generator as an optional second
    28|      * parameter.
    29|      *
    30|      * @param \Aws\Api\Service $service
    31|      * @param callable|null $bytesGenerator
    32|      *
    33|      * @return callable
    34|      */

    36|         Service $service,
    37|         ?callable $bytesGenerator = null
    38|     ) {
    39|         return function (callable $handler) use ($service, $bytesGenerator) {
    40|             return new self($handler, $service, $bytesGenerator);
    41|         };
    42|     }
    43|     public function __construct(

    43|     }
    44|     public function __invoke(CommandInterface $cmd) {
    45|         $nextHandler = $this->nextHandler;
    46|         $op = $this->service->getOperation($cmd->getName())->toArray();
    47|         if (!empty($op['input']['shape'])) {
    48|             $service = $this->service->toArray();
    49|             if (!empty($input = $service['shapes'][$op['input']['shape']])) {
    50|                 if (!empty($input['required'])) {
    51|                     foreach ($input['required'] as $key => $member) {
    52|                         if (in_array($member, $this->mandatoryAttributeList)) {
    53|                             $argument = is_string($cmd[$member]) ?  trim($cmd[$member]) : $cmd[$member];
    54|                             if ($argument === '' || $argument === null) {
    55|                                 $commandName = $cmd->getName();

    57|                                     "The {$commandName} operation requires non-empty parameter: {$member}"
    58|                                 );
    59|                             }
    60|                         }
    61|                     }
    62|                 }
    63|             }
    64|         }
    65|         return $nextHandler($cmd);

     7|  * A custom mutator for a GetBucketLocation request, which
     8|  * extract the bucket location value and injects it into the
     9|  * result as the `LocationConstraint` field.
    10|  *
    11|  * @internal
    12|  */
    13| final class GetBucketLocationResultMutator implements S3ResultMutator
    14| {
    15|     /**
    16|      * @inheritDoc
    17|      */
    18|     public function __invoke(
    19|         ResultInterface $result,
    20|         CommandInterface $command,
    21|         ResponseInterface $response
    22|     ): ResultInterface
    23|     {
    24|         if ($command->getName() !== 'GetBucketLocation') {
    25|             return $result;
    26|         }
    27|         static $location = 'us-east-1';
    28|         static $pattern = '/>(.+?)<\/LocationConstraint>/';
    29|         if (preg_match($pattern, $response->getBody(), $matches)) {
    30|             $location = $matches[1] === 'EU' ? 'eu-west-1' : $matches[1];
    31|         }
    32|         $result['LocationConstraint'] = $location;
    33|         $response->getBody()->rewind();
    34|         return $result;
    35|     }
    36| }

   265|     protected function ensureDirectoryExists(string $dirname, int $visibility): void
   266|     {
   267|         if (is_dir($dirname)) {
   268|             return;
   269|         }
   270|         error_clear_last();
   271|         if ( ! @mkdir($dirname, $visibility, true)) {
   272|             $mkdirError = error_get_last();
   273|         }
   274|         clearstatcache(true, $dirname);
   275|         if ( ! is_dir($dirname)) {
   276|             $errorMessage = isset($mkdirError['message']) ? $mkdirError['message'] : '';
   277|             throw UnableToCreateDirectory::atLocation($dirname, $errorMessage);
   278|         }
   279|     }

    11| /**
    12|  * @author Fedonyuk Anton <info@ensostudio.ru>
    13|  *
    14|  * @internal
    15|  */
    16| class PhpToken implements \Stringable
    17| {
    18|     /**
    19|      * @var int
    20|      */
    21|     public $id;
    22|     /**
    23|      * @var string
    24|      */
    25|     public $text;
    26|     /**
    27|      * @var int
    28|      */
    29|     public $line;
    30|     /**
    31|      * @var int
    32|      */
    33|     public $pos;
    34|     public function __construct(int $id, string $text, int $line = -1, int $position = -1)
    35|     {
    36|         $this->id = $id;
    37|         $this->text = $text;
    38|         $this->line = $line;
    39|         $this->pos = $position;
    40|     }
    41|     public function getTokenName(): ?string
    42|     {
    43|         if ('UNKNOWN' === $name = token_name($this->id)) {
    44|             $name = \strlen($this->text) > 1 || \ord($this->text) < 32 ? null : $this->text;
    45|         }
    46|         return $name;
    47|     }
    48|     /**
    49|      * @param int|string|array $kind
    50|      */
    51|     public function is($kind): bool
    52|     {
    53|         foreach ((array) $kind as $value) {
    54|             if (\in_array($value, [$this->id, $this->text], true)) {
    55|                 return true;
    56|             }
    57|         }
    58|         return false;
    59|     }
    60|     public function isIgnorable(): bool
    61|     {
    62|         return \in_array($this->id, [\T_WHITESPACE, \T_COMMENT, \T_DOC_COMMENT, \T_OPEN_TAG], true);
    63|     }
    64|     public function __toString(): string
    65|     {
    66|         return (string) $this->text;
    67|     }
    68|     /**
    69|      * @return static[]
    70|      */
    71|     public static function tokenize(string $code, int $flags = 0): array
    72|     {
    73|         $line = 1;
    74|         $position = 0;
    75|         $tokens = token_get_all($code, $flags);
    76|         foreach ($tokens as $index => $token) {
    77|             if (\is_string($token)) {
    78|                 $id = \ord($token);
    79|                 $text = $token;
    80|             } else {
    81|                 [$id, $text, $line] = $token;
    82|             }
    83|             $tokens[$index] = new static($id, $text, $line, $position);
    84|             $position += \strlen($text);
    85|         }
    86|         return $tokens;
    87|     }
    88| }

    72|     {

    78|         return false;
    79|     }
    80|     public static function array_all(array $array, callable $callback): bool
    81|     {
    82|         foreach ($array as $key => $value) {
    83|             if (!$callback($value, $key)) {
    84|                 return false;
    85|             }
    86|         }
    87|         return true;
    88|     }

   100|     }

    11| use Psr\Container\ContainerExceptionInterface;
    12| use Psr\Container\NotFoundExceptionInterface;
    13| class_exists(ContainerExceptionInterface::class);
    14| class_exists(NotFoundExceptionInterface::class);
    15| /**
    16|  * A trait to help implement ServiceProviderInterface.
    17|  *
    18|  * @author Robin Chalas <robin.chalas@gmail.com>
    19|  * @author Nicolas Grekas <p@tchwork.com>
    20|  */
    21| trait ServiceLocatorTrait
    22| {
    23|     private array $factories;
    24|     private array $loading = [];
    25|     private array $providedTypes;
    26|     /**
    27|      * @param array<string, callable> $factories
    28|      */
    29|     public function __construct(array $factories)
    30|     {
    31|         $this->factories = $factories;
    32|     }
    33|     public function has(string $id): bool
    34|     {
    35|         return isset($this->factories[$id]);
    36|     }
    37|     public function get(string $id): mixed
    38|     {
    39|         if (!isset($this->factories[$id])) {
    40|             throw $this->createNotFoundException($id);
    41|         }
    42|         if (isset($this->loading[$id])) {
    43|             $ids = array_values($this->loading);
    44|             $ids = \array_slice($this->loading, array_search($id, $ids));
    45|             $ids[] = $id;
    46|             throw $this->createCircularReferenceException($id, $ids);
    47|         }
    48|         $this->loading[$id] = $id;
    49|         try {
    50|             return $this->factories[$id]($this);
    51|         } finally {

# --- HUNK 2: Lines 57-95 ---
    57|         if (!isset($this->providedTypes)) {
    58|             $this->providedTypes = [];
    59|             foreach ($this->factories as $name => $factory) {
    60|                 if (!\is_callable($factory)) {
    61|                     $this->providedTypes[$name] = '?';
    62|                 } else {
    63|                     $type = (new \ReflectionFunction($factory))->getReturnType();
    64|                     $this->providedTypes[$name] = $type ? ($type->allowsNull() ? '?' : '').($type instanceof \ReflectionNamedType ? $type->getName() : $type) : '?';
    65|                 }
    66|             }
    67|         }
    68|         return $this->providedTypes;
    69|     }
    70|     private function createNotFoundException(string $id): NotFoundExceptionInterface
    71|     {
    72|         if (!$alternatives = array_keys($this->factories)) {
    73|             $message = 'is empty...';
    74|         } else {
    75|             $last = array_pop($alternatives);
    76|             if ($alternatives) {
    77|                 $message = sprintf('only knows about the "%s" and "%s" services.', implode('", "', $alternatives), $last);
    78|             } else {
    79|                 $message = sprintf('only knows about the "%s" service.', $last);
    80|             }
    81|         }
    82|         if ($this->loading) {
    83|             $message = sprintf('The service "%s" has a dependency on a non-existent service "%s". This locator %s', end($this->loading), $id, $message);
    84|         } else {
    85|             $message = sprintf('Service "%s" not found: the current service locator %s', $id, $message);
    86|         }
    87|         return new class($message) extends \InvalidArgumentException implements NotFoundExceptionInterface {
    88|         };
    89|     }
    90|     private function createCircularReferenceException(string $id, array $path): ContainerExceptionInterface
    91|     {
    92|         return new class(sprintf('Circular reference detected for service "%s", path: "%s".', $id, implode(' -> ', $path))) extends \RuntimeException implements ContainerExceptionInterface {
    93|         };
    94|     }

# --- HUNK 1: Lines 17-64 ---
    17|  *
    18|  * Service ids are available as "ClassName::methodName" so that the implementation
    19|  * of subscriber methods can be just `return $this->container->get(__METHOD__);`.
    20|  *
    21|  * @author Kevin Bond <kevinbond@gmail.com>
    22|  */
    23| trait ServiceMethodsSubscriberTrait
    24| {
    25|     protected ContainerInterface $container;
    26|     public static function getSubscribedServices(): array
    27|     {
    28|         $services = method_exists(get_parent_class(self::class) ?: '', __FUNCTION__) ? parent::getSubscribedServices() : [];
    29|         foreach ((new \ReflectionClass(self::class))->getMethods() as $method) {
    30|             if (self::class !== $method->getDeclaringClass()->name) {
    31|                 continue;
    32|             }
    33|             if (!$attribute = $method->getAttributes(SubscribedService::class)[0] ?? null) {
    34|                 continue;
    35|             }
    36|             if ($method->isStatic() || $method->isAbstract() || $method->isGenerator() || $method->isInternal() || $method->getNumberOfRequiredParameters()) {
    37|                 throw new \LogicException(sprintf('Cannot use "%s" on method "%s::%s()" (can only be used on non-static, non-abstract methods with no parameters).', SubscribedService::class, self::class, $method->name));
    38|             }
    39|             if (!$returnType = $method->getReturnType()) {
    40|                 throw new \LogicException(sprintf('Cannot use "%s" on methods without a return type in "%s::%s()".', SubscribedService::class, $method->name, self::class));
    41|             }
    42|             /* @var SubscribedService $attribute */
    43|             $attribute = $attribute->newInstance();
    44|             $attribute->key ??= self::class.'::'.$method->name;
    45|             $attribute->type ??= $returnType instanceof \ReflectionNamedType ? $returnType->getName() : (string) $returnType;
    46|             $attribute->nullable = $returnType->allowsNull();
    47|             if ($attribute->attributes) {
    48|                 $services[] = $attribute;
    49|             } else {
    50|                 $services[$attribute->key] = ($attribute->nullable ? '?' : '').$attribute->type;
    51|             }
    52|         }
    53|         return $services;
    54|     }
    55|     public function setContainer(ContainerInterface $container): ?ContainerInterface
    56|     {
    57|         $ret = null;
    58|         if (method_exists(get_parent_class(self::class) ?: '', __FUNCTION__)) {
    59|             $ret = parent::setContainer($container);
    60|         }
    61|         $this->container = $container;
    62|         return $ret;
    63|     }
    64| }

    30|             return false;

    24|             'src' => '',

    34|             'timestamp' => null

    37|         if (!$width && !$height) {
    38|             return ['error' => 'Target width or height parameter is missing'];
    39|         }

    49|                 }

    51|             }
    52|         }

    55|             $src = implode('/', array_filter(explode('/', $src), fn ($s) => trim($s, '.')));

    61|         }

    64|     protected function imageByAsset(array $options = [], bool $asPath = false, ?string $hash = null) {

    66|         $asset = null;
    67|         if (\str_starts_with($src, 'assets://')) {
